4 HJR___ RECOGNIZING THE DALE COUNTY SCHOOL SYSTEM FOR EARNING
5 A 95 OVERALL SCORE ON THE STATE AND FEDERAL ANNUAL REPORT
6 CARDS.
7
8 WHEREAS, it is fitting that we pay tribute to those
9 educational institutions that, through the natural talents
10 and unflagging commitment to academic excellence evidenced
11 by their administration, faculty, staff, and students, have
12 achieved state and federal recognition for excellence; and
13 WHEREAS, one such high-achieving educational system
14 is the Dale County School System, which earned a 95 overall
15 score on the Alabama State and Federal Report Cards, the
16 highest ever earned by a county school system in the history
17 of Alabama; the State and Federal Report Cards are the
18 measurement of the academic achievement and culture of
19 public school systems across the state and nation; and
20 WHEREAS, the dedication to academic excellence
21 demonstrated by all of the fine individuals affiliated with
22 the Dale County School System, including 3,200 students and
23 418 employees, is clearly deserving of our respect,
24 admiration, and commendation; and
25 WHEREAS, the individual schools that have contributed
26 to the success of public education in the communities across
27 Dale County and that are commended for their outstanding
28 achievement are Ariton School, Bridge Academy, Dale County
Page 1

achievement are Ariton School, Bridge Academy, Dale County
HJR63 INTRODUCED
29 High School, G.W. Long Elementary School, G.W. Long High
30 School, Midland City Elementary School, Newton Elementary
31 School, and South Dale Middle School; and
32 WHEREAS, Superintendent Ben Baker, who has served in
33 the Dale County School System for 30 years, has led the
34 school system to success by recognizing the importance of
35 creating an environment that encourages academic achievement
36 and by fostering strong partnerships with local business,
37 industry, and local churches; such community involvement has
38 helped reinforce a positive climate and culture where
39 students are motivated to attend, learn, and succeed,
40 supported by high-quality teachers and dedicated support
41 staff; now therefore,
42 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
43 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That we congratulate the Dale
44 County School System on receiving a 95 overall score on the
45 Alabama State and Federal Report Cards, and we extend to its
46 students, employees, and leadership our best wishes for
47 continued future success.
